race.comment: JUST GO BANG (3) led all the way and won a similar race here three runs back under just half a kilo less than he will carry today. Subsequent failures when he hasn't led may be worth overlooking. Deserves another chance. AFFERMATO (4) had been racing well before a comprehensive all-the-way win over 1800m here three weeks ago. Yet to prove himself at this trip but he showed no signs of slowing down last time. Races well at Hawkesbury and looks a serious threat again. MAGIC PHAROAH (10) is racing well without winning, the latest effort a closing fourth over 1800m in a Randwick Midway. One of the chances down in the weights. PRESLEY (5) warmed to the task late when resuming over 1800m at Rosehill a fortnight ago. Capable of sharp improvement up to this trip with that run under the belt. MEGA FIGHT (7) doesn't win often but his recent efforts, including a last start second when attempting this trip for the first time, have had merit.
